%F A006999 a(n) = A061419(n) - 1.
%F A006999 a(n) = A061418(n) - 2.
%F A006999 a(n) = floor((3a(n-1)+2)/2).
%F A006999 a(n) = -1 + floor(c*(3/2)^n) where c=1.0815136... - _Benoit Cloitre_, Jan 10 2002; this constant c is 2/3*K(3) (see A083286). - _Ralf Stephan_, May 29 2003
%F A006999 a(n+1) = (3*a(n))/2+1 if a(n) is even. a(n+1) = (3*a(n)+1)/2 if a(n) is odd. - _Miquel Cerda_, Jun 15 2019
%t A006999 a[0] = 0; a[n_] := a[n] = Floor[(3 a[n-1] + 2)/2];
